                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.118,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Sotomayor has our opinion this morning in case 13-975, T-Mobile South v. the City of Roswell."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.118,
                        "stop": 195.578,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15131,
                            "name": "Sonia Sotomayor",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/sonia_sotomayor",
                            "last_name": "Sotomayor",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2776,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 1249707600,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": null,
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2776"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32685,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 50379,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/sonia_sotomayor_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 2293,
                            "identifier": "sonia_sotomayor"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.118,
                                "stop": 14.87,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on writ of certiorari to the Court Of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 14.87,
                                "stop": 31.797,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "T-Mobile South applied to build a new 108 foot tall cell phone tower in the shape of an artificial tree on 2.8 acres of vacant residential property in the City of Roswell, Georgia."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 31.797,
                                "stop": 38.874,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "At a public city council hearing, council members expressed their concerns about the proposed tower."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 38.874,
                                "stop": 45.292,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The hearing ended with the council unanimously passing a motion to deny the application."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.292,
                                "stop": 60.225,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Two days later, the City\u0027s Planning and Zoning Division informed T-Mobile by letter that the application had been denied and that meeting minutes would be made available."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 60.225,
                                "stop": 64.619,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Detailed minutes were issued 26 days later."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 64.619,
                                "stop": 79.65,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "T-Mobile South sued in Federal District Court, which ruled in T-Mobile\u0027s favor and concluded that by failing to issue a written decision that stated the reasons for which the application had been denied,"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 79.65,
                                "stop": 94.586,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "the city violated a provision of the Telecommunications Act of 1996 that says that a locality\u0027s denial shall be in writing and supported by substantial evidence contained in a written record."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 94.586,
                                "stop": 97.105,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Eleventh Circuit reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 97.105,
                                "stop": 109.54,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We granted certiorari to resolve a circuit split about whether and in what form localities must provide reasons when they deny applications like T-Mobile\u0027s."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 109.54,
                                "stop": 129.311,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "For the reasons stated in our opinion we hold that the Act requires localities to provide or make available their reasons in writing but we also conclude that nothing in the Act requires those reasons to appear specifically in a locality\u0027s written denial letter."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 129.311,
                                "stop": 143.876,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Rather a locality may comply with its statutory reason giving obligation if it provides its reasons in some other written record and in a fashion that is clear enough to enable judicial review."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.876,
                                "stop": 159.912,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "However, a locality cannot stymie or burden that judicial review by delaying substantially the release of its reasons and must provide in writing reasons at essentially the same time as it communicates its denial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 159.912,
                                "stop": 172.902,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "While the city provided its reasons in writing and did so in the acceptable form of detailed minute meetings it did not provide those reasons essentially contemporaneously with its written denial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 172.902,
                                "stop": 178.837,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Accordingly, we reversed the judgment of the Eleventh Circuit and remand for further proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 178.837,
                                "stop": 191.442,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has filed a concurring opinion, the Chief Justice has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justice Ginsburg joins and in which Justice Thomas joins as to part one."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 191.442,
                                "stop": 195.578,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas has filed a dissenting opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
